ce:section.ce:para:
In a large number of malignant lesions, the area identified on B-mode as the hypoechoic mass does not code on SWE because a shear wave is not identified or may code with a low cs. Bai found that 63% of breast malignancies have this finding (Bai, Du et al. 2012). Preliminary evaluation of this phenomenon suggests that shear waves may not propagate as expected in some cancers (Barr 2012) (Figure 8
                           ). The shear waves in these tumors demonstrate significant noise that may be incorrectly interpreted as a low SWS by the system. The addition of a quality measure that evaluates the shear waves generated and determines if they are adequate for an accurate cs measurement will help in eliminating possible false negative cases (Barr 2014, Barr 2012) (Figure 9
                           ).
